In a large bowl, combine the first nine ingredients; mix well. Cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs. In another bowl, whisk the egg, yogurt and milk. Stir into dry ingredients until just moistened. Spoon into a 9-in. round baking pan coated with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle with poppy seeds. Bake at 400 degrees F for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool in pan on a wire rack. Cut into wedges.